I.	Introduction
A Risk Management Program has been implemented at the Michael Lewis Company (Michael Lewis), McCook, Illinois, for the reduction of accidental releases of hazardous materials. This Program summarizes the management, administrative, procedural, and technological controls that work together to minimize the risk to site personnel, contractors, visitors, and the community and environment at large of hazardous chemical releases. This five-year Risk Management Plan (RMP) resubmittal is organized to correspond with specific U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) RMP, Program 3 of 40 CFR 68, definitions and requirements of Subpart G, including:

	Introduction;
	Michael Lewis policies to protect health, environment, and safety;
	Facility identification and regulated substances covered processes;
	Hazard Assessment;
	Prevention Program;
	Five-Year Accident History;
	Emergency Response Plan; 
	Emergency Communications;
	Spill Reporting / Environmental Release Procedures;
	Planned changes to improve safety; and
	Management Program

II.	Michael Lewis Policies to Protect Health, Environment, and Safety
Risk management and safety are important concerns at Michael Lewis; this RMP formalizes and documents these activities. Michael Lewis is committed to conducting its operations in a safe and responsible manner and to reducing risks to human health and to the environment. It is Michael Lewis policy to comply with all applicable federal, state, and local rules and regulations.

